two democratic senators say theyll keep 8000 
in campaign contributions from an importedcar dealers group even 
though both complained the organization is a foreign agent forbidden 
to make such payments 
although the auto dealers and drivers free trade pac gave 5000 
to sen bob graham of florida and 3000 to sen harry reid of 
nevada last year it also spent nearly 1 million to defeat them and 
sen richard bryan dnev 
those three senators along with sen david boren dokla 
signed a letter to the justice department asking it to investigate 
whether the pac ought to be registered as a foreign agent 
