otero then spotted mrs gee and her family at a pay phone calling 
a cousin for directions the new york times reported in todays 
editions 
the family mrs gees husband allious 74 her grandson 
cedrick 4 and her children from a previous marriage joel hardy 
29 an army staff sergeant stationed in germany and barbi hardy 18 
had left north carolina early thursday afternoon for the funeral 
of mrs gees uncle in new york city 
the gunman forced the family to drive him to long island 
for a while the times said otero had the pistol aimed at joel 
hardys head as hardy tried to find a way to long island part of 
the time he methodically loaded the gun and licked the tip of each 
bullet before shoving it into the pistol chamber the times quoted 
barbi hardy as saying 
now i can shoot you all miss hardy recalled the gunman 
saying one mistake and ill shoot the boy in the head 
the gunman forced the family out of the car on the long island 
expressway police said perrone said there were no reports of 
injuries to the family or vazquez 
otero then fled on foot he contacted his relatives while on the 
run and was talked into giving himself up perrone said 
