<TEXT>
to haunting strains of a newly composed 
hymn polish farmers gathered with a sense of vindication today for 
the first national congress in eight years of their banned union 
rural solidarity 
we meet here in a dramatic situation rural solidarity 
chairman jozef slisz said the national economy is destroyed 
people in towns and villages live on the edge of poverty but this 
is our country we have to save it for ourselves and our children 
the congress brought together farmers from every region of the 
country plus foreign guests and a visit from lech walesa chairman 
of the allied independent workers union solidarity 
it took place even before the end of talks between the opposition 
and communist authorities which have yielded agreement in principle 
to legalize solidarity rural solidarity and the independent 
students association 
all three were banned after martial law was introduced december 
1981 on tuesday parliament will consider draft legislation to 
legalize them again 
during those eight years which we spent in prison or in 
hiding we did not forget the ideals of solidarity some of our 
colleagues paid with their lives slisz said 
we can meet again after eight years thanks to mr walesa 
thanks to his persistence and determination he is the symbol of 
solidarity for cities and villages the hall erupted into chants 
of solidarnosc solidarnosc when walesa appeared 
my role has been to lead you to this point so that you can 
meet and decide about your own activities walesa told them 
many farmers had traveled on overnight trains or slept in cars to 
be on hand for the opening mass at a modern church on warsaws 
northern outskirts 
artur balazs a member of rural solidaritys national council 
said 450 delegates were attending with 50 invited guests and 
advisers 
they met in a basement hall of the church dominated by a banner 
proclaiming the national congress of rural solidarity 198189 
slisz said the congress must ensure that rural solidarity is 
legalized and prepare for national elections of the union in 
december 
the rev jan bijak told farmers to draw inspiration for their 
reborn organization from traditional values that made peasant 
farmers the backbone of the nation in a new hymn composed for the 
congress an altar assistant then sang mother lead us to your 
son through our beloved soil 
