the israeli leader plans to visit washington in april and is 
expected to come under increasing pressure from us officials to 
produce new ideas for a peace initiative 
washington recently launched a dialogue with the plo and 
secretary of state james baker iii said tuesday that israel may have 
no alternative but to reverse its policy and negotiate with the 
guerrillas it calls terrorists 
shamir 73 reiterated in an interview published friday in 
jerusalem that he will never talk to the plo and rejects giving up 
the occupied gaza strip and west bank in exchange for peace a 
concept at the heart of us middle east policy 
cabinet minister mordechai gur a labor party leader helping to 
organize the conference said the meeting will not be used to 
legitimize or boost shamirs rightwing positions gurs 
leftofcenter party is a partner in the national unity government 
headed by shamir of the likud bloc 
it is not going to be a shamir conference it is not going to 
be a likud conference it is going to be a jewish conference in 
support of the state of israel of the government of the state of 
israel said gur who has no portfolio 
like a small number of other labor ministers gur has publicly 
supported talks with the plo under certain conditions 
ehud olmert the cabinet minister in charge of arab affairs who 
is from likud said the conference was called precisely because 
there are divisions among israelis and jews outside the country 
about the peace process 
we believe it is important at this particular time to reaffirm 
solidarity for the state of israel there will not be any specific 
resolution calling for support for a particular policy line he 
said 
israel has faced mounting international criticism because of 
harsh methods the army uses to suppress the palestinian revolt 
against israeli occupation now in its 16th month 
at least 395 palestinians have been killed during the uprising 
most from israeli army gunfire seventeen israelis also have died 
some jewish circles also are critical a recent poll conducted by 
the american jewish committee showed american jews still support 
israel but they are embarrassed by its actions against palestinian 
rioters 
a spokesman for the antidefamation league of bnai brith a new 
yorkbased jewish service organization said the conference is 
designed to counter the impression that criticism of israel by jews 
means they have abandoned support for the state 
we believe that too many enemies of israel have mistaken 
the open communal discussion of israels current difficulties and 
the legitimate differences within our own community as a withdrawal 
of our general support for israel it says in a statement to be 
published in sundays jerusalem post 
among leaders expected at the conference are morris abrams 
