inc after the labor department said wholesale prices surged 10 
percent in february if this shocks you into thinking we have an 
inflation problem thats right 
the report this past friday matched a jump in january and 
translated into an annual wholesale inflation rate exceeding 12 
percent more than triple the level of last year 
it incited one of the biggest setbacks of the year for the stock 
and bond markets where prices tumbled on fear that inflation is 
eroding the value of these investments and will require a stiff 
curative dose of higher interest rates orchestrated by the federal 
reserve the nations central bank 
the prospect of sharply tighter credit in turn signaled a range 
of potential consequences that included higher mortgage rates more 
loan defaults and rising unemployment possible elements of a 
recession 
if you hold debt thats based on an adjustrable rate it will 
raise your monthly expenses said michael moran a strategist at 
